Based on the repository analysis of the OffChat project, here are the documented requirements tailored specifically to this codebase (Kotlin, SQLDelight, Compose, and P2P Networking).

3.5.1 Developer Requirements
3.5.1.1 Hardware Requirements

To support the development, compilation, and testing of the OffChat Kotlin Multiplatform/Android application, the following hardware configuration is recommended:

Processor: Intel Core i5 / AMD Ryzen 5 or higher (Hexa-core recommended for fast Gradle daemon execution).

RAM: Minimum 16 GB (Android Studio and the Gradle build system for Kotlin Multiplatform are memory-intensive).

Storage: At least 512 GB SSD (High-speed NVMe preferred to reduce build times and handle large .gradle caches).

Physical Testing Devices: At least two physical Android devices are required to test peer-to-peer (P2P) discovery and messaging, as Android Emulators do not fully support Wi-Fi Direct or Bluetooth hardware abstraction.

Network Interfaces: Dual-band Wi-Fi and Bluetooth 5.0+ support.

3.5.1.2 Software Requirements

The system is built using the modern Android/Kotlin stack designed for local-first, secure communication. The required software includes:

Operating System: Windows 10/11, macOS (Sonoma or later), or Linux (Ubuntu 22.04 LTS).

Development Framework: Kotlin Multiplatform (KMP) & Jetpack Compose.

IDE / Code Editor: Android Studio (Ladybug or newer) with the Kotlin and Compose plugins installed.

Build Tool: Gradle 8.10.2 or higher.

Programming Languages: Kotlin (Standard for both UI and Logic).

Database Tooling: SQLDelight (for type-safe local persistence generation).

Networking Stack: Google Nearby Connections API / Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE).

Dependency Injection: Koin (Android/Kotlin core).

Security Library: Java Cryptography Architecture (JCA) for AES/RSA implementation.

Version Control: Git.

3.5.2 User Requirements

To use the OffChat application for decentralized messaging, the user’s device must meet the following criteria:

Device: Android smartphone with hardware support for Wi-Fi Direct and Bluetooth.

Operating System: Android 8.0 (Oreo / API 26) or above (required for modern Foreground Service and Notification Channel support).

Connectivity: Both Bluetooth and Wi-Fi must be toggled ON (Internet access is not required for messaging, but required for the initial app download).

Storage: Minimum free storage of 50 MB for the application and local SQL database.

Permissions Required:

Nearby Devices: To discover and connect to peers (Required for Android 12+).

Location Services: Required by the Android system for Bluetooth/Wi-Fi scanning.

Notifications: To maintain the NearbyForegroundService and alert users of new messages.

Camera (Optional): If the application implements QR code pairing for secure key exchange.

Storage access: To save and share media files within chats.




